			<div><strong>spell book with spell names and stats</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>Hi,<br />
<br />
First of I have no idea how to make stuff for the new UI :-( and no time to learn it either.<br />
<br />
I heard though that it consist of XML language. This would imply I think that you can make it dynamic. Would it then be possible to make a spell book (I'm a druid you see) that shows, as soon as you scribe a spel into it, the name and summarised stats of that spell, in a couple of lines under the scribed spell itself?<br />
<br />
EQcaster proggy used to pick this information from Verants own spell file in the EQ directory (this proggy has not been updated yet to read the new spell icons). I would suspect that this should also be possibly used for such a customised spell book.<br />
<br />
If anybody would like to undertake this task to make such, I'd be much obliged. Or else tell me that it is'nt hard at all and that I would be able to learn how to do so in a couple of hours?<br />
<br />
Marco (RL)<br />
Paithan (EQ) (24druid terris thule)</div>
